result.execSummary:
The defendant Mariah M Duenkel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes:
$243 court costs imposed in Ct. 1 shall be paid as a condition of probation in Ct. 2 or judgment shall be entered for nonpayment.  
If probation or extended supervision is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription.  
Defendant shall not associate with known drug users or be present where drugs are illegally purchased, sold or consumed.

Defendant shall provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge; Court informs Defendant of DNA expungement rights.
Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.
Defendant shall submit to random drug screens including blood, breath or urine.
